    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - ELECTRONIC ENGINES, CATERPILLAR C-10 AND C-12
        ENGINES - TROUBLESHOOTING - Important Steps Before Testing
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Important Steps Before Testing</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <emph type="bold">Gather information</emph>
                by talking to the driver if possible. Try to determine the exact symptoms by gathering relevant
                information:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">What happened and when?</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Under what conditions?</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">When did the symptoms begin?</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">What else occurred at that time?</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <emph type="bold">Verify the problem.</emph>
                Is the complaint due to misunderstood customer selected parameters? Use an EST to review customer
                selected parameters.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <emph type="bold">Check for and record</emph>
                any logged fault codes.
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Do the logged codes correlate to probable causes?</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Were the codes logged about the same time as the symptoms appeared? Were the codes
                    logged repeatedly?
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Are the logged codes related to other symptoms? Do they have a common cause?</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <emph type="bold">Avoid Preconceived Ideas!</emph>
                Eliminate any non-electrical causes for the problem first (contaminated fuel, clogged air filters,
                etc.).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
